Buns are what hamburgers and hot dogs go on.  They're soft and not crispy.  They are a subset of a larger category called rolls, which are any single-serving sized piece of bread, whether they are small dinner rolls, Kaiser rolls, onion rolls, Portuguese rolls, hard rolls...

But not all rolls are buns.  Only the soft kind for hamburgers and hot dogs are buns.

@Steve L 

Right. So please substitute roll for bun in my previous post. I don't get the distinction because it does not exist in Polish, and when I was learning English almost 40 years ago, I was taught bun=bułka.

So... in Polish bread in the broad sense is pieczywo, and it is divided into bread in the narrow sense - chleb (loaves, where a slice is a serving) and rolls - bułki (singular bułka), where the whole thing is a single serving.

