(More useless facts about Polish bread: A typical item at a Polish bakery is bułka wrocławska - Wrocław roll. The thing is, it is a loaf, pretty much the size and shape of chleb. I'm thinking the reason may be that traditionally all chleb in Poland was sourdough, and rolls were not. Perhaps bułka wrocławska is a bułka rather than a chleb, despite its size and shape, because it does not involve sourdough? hm...)

