I started with Yes, then changed that to YeP, before finally realizing it would be YUP. Quite the journey for such a short word 🤣

It's quite interesting how often American English will have more viable spelling variants of a certain word than Polish. Take "yes". In Polish that's "tak," and in slang we may shorten that to "ta," but that's it. Compare that to yes, yep, yup, yeah. Of course, we have other completely different ways of saying we agree, the most common being "ano," confusingly for English speakers shortened to "no" (and related to the Czech and Slovak "ano"). But it's not a variant of "yes" as such.

